{
  "texts": [
    "Besides the customer experience, online and offline channel also differ from a data and modelling perspective as briefly expounded in the following.",
    "• Data availability: Online channels profit from increased availability of customer related information and data.",
    "The former is typically obtained from customer profiles comprising information such as age, gender, and location.",
    "The latter mostly consists of historic click and purchase behaviour of the customer.",
    "The availability of such personal data allows for personalization in online channels."
  ]
}